headline: Will Williams’ 2025 Earnings Beat, 2026 Outlook and Dividend Hike Change Williams Companies' (WMB) Narrative?
summary: In February 2026, The Williams Companies, Inc. reported full-year 2025 results showing revenue of US$11.95 billion and net income of US$2.62 billion, with basic and diluted earnings per share of US$2.14, up from US$1.82 a year earlier. The company also issued a strong 2026 earnings outlook tied to new pipeline and offshore projects and announced a 5% dividend increase, prompting broadly positive analyst reactions despite a mixed fourth-quarter performance.
